text: Marina del Rey is an unincorporated community and census-designated place (CDP) in Los Angeles County, California, United States. The population was 11,373 at the 2020 census. The Marina, the world's largest man-made small craft harbor with eight basins having a capacity for 5,300 boats and is home port to about 6,500 boats. ==References== Category:Unincorporated communities in California Category:Census-designated places in California Category:Settlements in Los Angeles County, California
